{"add":{"doc":{"id":"e92700fbbe371016824f980177954378349a8fa47d8a24f237987d1bc0bafce9","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/ActorsPerformForTroops1.jpg/220px-ActorsPerformForTroops1.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Monroe and Joe DiMaggio were married in San Francisco on January 14, 1954. They traveled to Japan soon after, combining a honeymoon with a business trip previously arranged by DiMaggio. For two weeks she took a secondary role to DiMaggio as he conducted his business, having told a reporter, \"Marriage is my main career from now on.\"[80] Monroe then traveled alone to Korea where she performed for 13,000 American Marines over a three-day period. She later commented that the experience had helped her overcome a fear of performing in front of large crowds.[81]"]}}}